ğŸ“š Learning Outcomes
By using this virtual lab, a learner will understand:
- How memory works in C  
- How pointers reference values  
- How loops generate patterns  
- How arrays & strings behave  
- How functions are declared & executed  
- Why `fgets()` is safer than `scanf("%s")`  
- Why infinite `while(1)` loops work  
- How modular C projects are organized  

